<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-12-08T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-12-08T20:00:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6838: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-09T09:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">December 9,
                                        1925—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 9—2:24
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>521. My 517, December 7, 10 a.m. Following from American consul, Mukden:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“December 8, 1 p.m. Chang and his son are determined to make hard
                                    fight. Young Chang has a strong position on the Liao. There is
                                    still a small possibility that the Marshal can hold on. The city
                                    quiet.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>